WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:20.000
[Outdoor test area. Two wooden structures side by side: "RAW LUMBER" on left, "M-FIRE TREATED LUMBER" on right. On-screen timer begins.]

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:50.000
[Fire ignited simultaneously inside both structures. Flames begin to grow.]

00:00:50.000 --> 00:01:30.000
[RAW LUMBER structure: flames spread rapidly through the wood frame.]

00:01:30.000 --> 00:02:30.000
[M-FIRE TREATED structure: fire burns initial kindling. Flames do not spread to treated lumber.]

00:02:30.000 --> 00:03:30.000
[RAW LUMBER structure fully engulfed in flames. Structural integrity failing.]

00:03:30.000 --> 00:04:30.000
[M-FIRE TREATED structure: kindling burns out. Fire begins to self-extinguish.]

00:04:30.000 --> 00:05:30.000
[RAW LUMBER structure continues burning intensely. M-FIRE TREATED structure fire fully extinguished.]

00:05:30.000 --> 00:06:30.000
[RAW LUMBER structure reduced to charred frame. M-FIRE TREATED structure remains structurally intact.]

00:06:30.000 --> 00:07:30.000
[Fire in RAW LUMBER structure diminishing as fuel is exhausted. Smoke continues.]

00:07:30.000 --> 00:08:30.000
[Firefighter enters with hose and extinguishes remaining embers in RAW LUMBER structure.]

00:08:30.000 --> 00:08:57.000
[Final comparison: RAW LUMBER structure destroyed. M-FIRE TREATED structure intact. Test concludes at 8:57.]

00:08:57.000 --> 00:09:00.000
[Black screen with M-Fire Suppression contact information.]
